I find it interesting that this site is getting press.  If that is what it takes to keep it up and running, bravo!<br>
More exposure is certainly what it needs.<br>
As for the folks on this other site; I think that like a lot of academia they are speaking what they were taught. The thing that I find puzzeling is the unwillingness to speak to another side of an issue.  Is there no room for growth?<br>
Like this young man who posted here with all the praise for his guru, Kali Tai.  I find it worrisome that this youngster who has probably never seen a body bag or what goes into one,  echoes the biases of the elite scholars that frequent this site. <br>
Personally, I could give a flying fiddely f**k if I ever have to interface with any of these yo-yo's.<br>
These folks are so entrenched in their beliefs of the war and the warriors that they don't have time for an alternate point of view.  Beliefs that have been adhered to and supported over the time span of 30 years are difficult to change or erase.<br>
I ain't got the time or the energy to screw with an entire site's head,  BUT if all of us did it!!!   What fun this could be!
